1
00:00:10,867 --> 00:00:11,867
<i> I don't want it here.</i>

2
00:00:12,000 --> 00:00:13,600
<i>It'll drive me crazy
even more.</i>

3
00:00:15,067 --> 00:00:18,533
<i>Madam, you've come
to the right person.</i>

4
00:00:18,667 --> 00:00:19,233
<i> Jade?</i>

5
00:00:19,367 --> 00:00:21,533
<i> I just miss Mom.</i>

6
00:00:21,667 --> 00:00:22,567
<i> Me, too, dear.</i>

7
00:00:22,700 --> 00:00:23,900
<i> I miss your mom, too.</i>

8
00:00:24,033 --> 00:00:27,533
<i>They'll kill you.
Don't let them kill you.</i>

9
00:00:30,033 --> 00:00:31,533
<i> Emma! Mookie!</i>

10
00:00:31,667 --> 00:00:33,167
<i>- I'll kill you all!
- Emma!</i>

11
00:00:33,300 --> 00:00:34,400
<i> I'll kill you all!</i>

12
00:00:34,567 --> 00:00:35,700
<i> Put her inside.</i>

13
00:00:35,833 --> 00:00:37,067
<i> That's Emma.</i>

14
00:00:37,200 --> 00:00:40,333
<i>Maybe it's better if you
don't visit Emma for now.</i>

15
00:00:40,467 --> 00:00:42,500
<i>It's also for
Mookie's safety.</i>

16
00:00:42,867 --> 00:00:43,833
<i> Who are you?</i>

17
00:00:44,567 --> 00:00:47,000
<i>- Why do you keep on calling...
- How are you, Jade Caparas?</i>

18
00:00:47,133 --> 00:00:48,600
<i> I've finally found you.</i>

19
00:00:48,733 --> 00:00:52,567
<i>The one you like
isn't meant for you.</i>

20
00:00:52,700 --> 00:00:55,333
<i>Because someone else
already owns him.</i>

21
00:01:34,400 --> 00:01:35,100
Jade.

22
00:01:37,500 --> 00:01:41,633
- I'm sorry, I don't...
- It's okay, it's okay.

23
00:01:41,800 --> 00:01:44,100
I know we're both vulnerable.

24
00:01:44,633 --> 00:01:51,167
It would be better
if forget what happened.

25
00:01:53,267 --> 00:01:58,567
Maybe it's better
if we go out with Mookie.

26
00:01:58,700 --> 00:02:01,200
Let's do something,

27
00:02:01,333 --> 00:02:05,433
so you can take a break
from thinking about Emma.

28
00:02:05,567 --> 00:02:06,633
Sure.

29
00:02:06,767 --> 00:02:09,600
Whatever you think is best,
Jade.

30
00:02:09,733 --> 00:02:11,900
I'll just change my clothes.

31
00:02:12,033 --> 00:02:13,000
Okay.

32
00:02:16,000 --> 00:02:21,533
<i>Just one more step and you'll
finally fall into my trap.</i>

33
00:02:37,633 --> 00:02:41,600
Oh, so you want
to play hide and seek.

34
00:02:41,733 --> 00:02:44,067
Okay, so you can
be able to eat...

35
00:02:44,200 --> 00:02:45,600
Come here.

36
00:02:45,733 --> 00:02:47,000
This way.

37
00:02:47,167 --> 00:02:51,000
I'll remove your jacket,
but be a good girl.

38
00:02:51,133 --> 00:02:54,233
Don't do anything bad.

39
00:02:58,767 --> 00:03:01,500
So you can eat.

40
00:03:01,633 --> 00:03:03,600
I'm sure you're already hungry.

41
00:03:04,667 --> 00:03:06,633
Just be a good girl, okay?

42
00:03:16,400 --> 00:03:17,733
I'll kill you.

43
00:03:20,433 --> 00:03:23,033
Believe me, Flor.

44
00:03:23,200 --> 00:03:27,600
Emma is a patient here
in my workplace,

45
00:03:27,733 --> 00:03:30,833
in Haven Woods Sanctuary.

46
00:03:33,067 --> 00:03:34,633
Where are you?

47
00:03:34,767 --> 00:03:37,600
I'm on my way
to the place you texted me.

48
00:03:37,733 --> 00:03:40,133
Are you sure it was Emma?

49
00:03:40,267 --> 00:03:42,067
Yes, Flor.

50
00:03:42,200 --> 00:03:43,300
Come on.

51
00:03:43,433 --> 00:03:46,133
I clearly remember
Emma's face.

52
00:03:46,267 --> 00:03:49,367
You know, she's so pitiful.

53
00:03:49,500 --> 00:03:51,733
I don't think
she's getting better.

54
00:03:51,867 --> 00:03:53,833
She's even getting worse.

55
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:55,233
Sefa?

56
00:03:55,367 --> 00:03:56,033
Sefa?

57
00:03:59,900 --> 00:04:02,067
You can't catch me.

58
00:04:02,200 --> 00:04:03,633
- You can't catch me.
- Hello, Flor?

59
00:04:03,767 --> 00:04:05,633
- You can't catch me.
- Hello.

60
00:04:05,767 --> 00:04:07,667
- Hello?
- You can't catch me.

61
00:04:13,333 --> 00:04:14,333
Emma?

62
00:04:15,833 --> 00:04:16,933
Hey!

63
00:04:17,067 --> 00:04:18,767
Where's Emma?

64
00:04:18,900 --> 00:04:20,233
She ran outside.

65
00:04:20,367 --> 00:04:23,800
Come on! Hurry up!
Let's catch her!

66
00:04:23,933 --> 00:04:25,933
Is that you, Emma?

67
00:04:26,067 --> 00:04:26,933
Help me.

68
00:04:27,100 --> 00:04:28,100
Help me!

69
00:04:28,233 --> 00:04:30,900
They're following me!
They'll kill me!

70
00:04:33,900 --> 00:04:35,600
Okay.

71
00:04:35,733 --> 00:04:36,633
You'll help me?

72
00:04:42,233 --> 00:04:43,900
Hey!

73
00:04:44,033 --> 00:04:47,300
Did you see
our patient pass by?

74
00:04:47,433 --> 00:04:49,667
- No.
- The one we're trying to catch.

75
00:04:49,800 --> 00:04:50,633
I'm sorry,

76
00:04:50,767 --> 00:04:51,400
- I didn't notice anyone.
- Are you sure?

77
00:04:51,533 --> 00:04:53,133
No. I didn't see anyone.

78
00:04:53,267 --> 00:04:54,900
What are you still doing here?

79
00:04:55,033 --> 00:04:57,400
Find her! You're so useless!

80
00:05:35,067 --> 00:05:36,000
Hurry up!

81
00:05:36,133 --> 00:05:37,700
Hurry up, Emma!

82
00:05:41,767 --> 00:05:42,933
Emma!

83
00:05:43,067 --> 00:05:45,000
Don't you remember me?

84
00:05:45,133 --> 00:05:46,867
I'm Sefa.

85
00:05:47,000 --> 00:05:50,300
I'm Ma'am Olive's former
house helper.

86
00:05:50,433 --> 00:05:52,233
I know Flor.

87
00:05:52,367 --> 00:05:53,600
Emma!

88
00:05:55,500 --> 00:05:58,867
I'm not sure
if I'm doing the right thing.

89
00:05:59,000 --> 00:06:01,633
But do you have a place to go?

90
00:06:01,767 --> 00:06:03,767
I'm worried about you.

91
00:06:03,900 --> 00:06:05,400
Something might happen to you.

92
00:06:05,533 --> 00:06:06,300
Emma!

93
00:06:06,433 --> 00:06:07,767
Wait!

94
00:06:07,933 --> 00:06:09,133
Emma!

95
00:06:09,267 --> 00:06:11,200
- Hey!
- There she is!

96
00:06:11,333 --> 00:06:13,733
- Emma!
- There she is! Hurry up!

97
00:06:22,500 --> 00:06:24,833
Do you think
we won't find you there?

98
00:06:24,967 --> 00:06:27,567
Come here.

99
00:06:27,700 --> 00:06:30,833
- Do you think you can escape?
- Devil!

100
00:06:30,967 --> 00:06:34,067
- In your dreams!
- Devil!

101
00:06:34,200 --> 00:06:39,167
I told you, you'll die here!

102
00:06:39,300 --> 00:06:40,533
Ouch!

103
00:06:40,700 --> 00:06:41,733
Help me!

104
00:07:26,733 --> 00:07:29,500
Ouch! Help me!

105
00:07:29,633 --> 00:07:31,200
Ouch!

106
00:07:43,967 --> 00:07:46,900
Don't come near me!
Leave me alone!

107
00:07:47,033 --> 00:07:50,000
No! Stop it! Please!

108
00:07:50,167 --> 00:07:52,700
Stop!

109
00:07:52,833 --> 00:07:55,933
I don't want it!

110
00:07:56,067 --> 00:07:58,933
Stop it!

111
00:08:05,667 --> 00:08:06,800
Help me.

112
00:08:15,900 --> 00:08:19,133
The patient's other test results
will come out tomorrow.

113
00:08:20,133 --> 00:08:22,233
Are you sure
you won't return her

114
00:08:22,400 --> 00:08:24,133
to Haven Woods Psychiatric
Sanctuary?

115
00:08:24,667 --> 00:08:25,967
Not now, Doctor.

116
00:08:27,200 --> 00:08:28,333
And...

117
00:08:29,367 --> 00:08:30,567
if...

118
00:08:31,500 --> 00:08:32,800
it's possible...

119
00:08:33,400 --> 00:08:37,367
please don't tell anyone
that the patient is here.

120
00:08:38,433 --> 00:08:40,167
Okay, Logan.

121
00:08:41,133 --> 00:08:44,833
I'll update you tomorrow
on the patient's condition.

122
00:08:46,867 --> 00:08:51,600
We'll also discuss the possible
treatment regimen for her.

123
00:08:51,733 --> 00:08:52,700
Okay.

124
00:09:07,600 --> 00:09:08,433
Marco,

125
00:09:09,833 --> 00:09:11,933
like I told you,

126
00:09:12,067 --> 00:09:14,433
I want to know
who this woman is.

127
00:09:14,900 --> 00:09:18,400
Boss, someone might look
for that woman.

128
00:09:18,533 --> 00:09:20,333
We might get charged.

129
00:09:20,467 --> 00:09:22,400
That's why you're here.

130
00:09:23,667 --> 00:09:26,033
You'll clean up all my mess.

131
00:09:28,367 --> 00:09:31,767
I just can't explain
why I'm interested in her.

132
00:09:34,233 --> 00:09:36,133
There you go again, boss.

133
00:09:36,267 --> 00:09:39,567
That's also
how you were with Jade.

134
00:09:39,700 --> 00:09:43,467
You love saving women.

135
00:09:43,600 --> 00:09:47,933
You might go crazy,
like what happened to Jade.

136
00:09:50,400 --> 00:09:51,700
Ouch.

137
00:09:52,167 --> 00:09:54,933
Just do what I tell you.

138
00:09:55,467 --> 00:09:57,333
Do you understand?

139
00:09:57,933 --> 00:09:59,767
- Yes.
- Do it, okay?

140
00:09:59,900 --> 00:10:01,467
Yes, boss.

141
00:10:01,633 --> 00:10:02,700
Go on.

142
00:10:21,600 --> 00:10:24,833
- Flor!
- Where's Emma?

143
00:10:24,967 --> 00:10:28,833
Flor, I was able to help
Emma escape.

144
00:10:28,967 --> 00:10:31,233
But she fainted on the street.

145
00:10:31,367 --> 00:10:33,300
And a man took her.

146
00:10:33,433 --> 00:10:34,567
He put her in his car.

147
00:10:34,733 --> 00:10:36,333
- What?
- Yes.

148
00:10:36,467 --> 00:10:38,267
How can we follow Emma?

149
00:10:38,400 --> 00:10:39,433
Don't worry.

150
00:10:39,567 --> 00:10:40,700
I took a video of it.

151
00:10:40,833 --> 00:10:43,967
Here. Look at it.

152
00:10:44,100 --> 00:10:47,033
How did Emma
get into Haven Wood?

153
00:10:47,167 --> 00:10:49,300
What happened to her?

154
00:10:49,433 --> 00:10:51,333
Where's Mookie?

155
00:10:58,433 --> 00:11:00,233
I left my phone in the car.

156
00:11:00,367 --> 00:11:02,633
- Go ahead. I'll just get it.
- Okay.

157
00:11:08,633 --> 00:11:11,200
How are you?

158
00:11:11,333 --> 00:11:13,133
How dare you touch me?

159
00:11:13,267 --> 00:11:15,233
Who are you? I don't know you!

160
00:11:15,367 --> 00:11:17,067
I'll call security!

161
00:11:17,200 --> 00:11:20,267
Don't you miss my hugs?

162
00:11:20,400 --> 00:11:22,500
What are you
talking about?

163
00:11:22,633 --> 00:11:23,733
I don't even know you!

164
00:11:25,200 --> 00:11:26,267
You don't know me?

165
00:11:28,300 --> 00:11:29,400
Or are you just pretending

166
00:11:29,533 --> 00:11:32,667
that you don't remember
Logan Alvarez?

167
00:11:32,800 --> 00:11:37,433
The man who helped you
from the yakuza in Japan.

168
00:11:38,767 --> 00:11:43,733
You had nothing
when I helped you.

169
00:11:43,900 --> 00:11:46,200
But what did you do in return?

170
00:11:46,333 --> 00:11:51,067
You disappeared after
you drained me of money.

171
00:11:51,200 --> 00:11:54,100
You don't answer my calls.

172
00:11:54,233 --> 00:11:57,267
So you're the man
who keeps on calling me.

173
00:11:57,400 --> 00:11:59,100
Why are you here?

174
00:11:59,233 --> 00:12:02,400
To tell me you're still
so in love with me?

175
00:12:02,533 --> 00:12:04,767
Welcome back, Logan!

176
00:12:04,900 --> 00:12:06,133
But guess what?

177
00:12:06,267 --> 00:12:08,133
I've moved on from you.

178
00:12:08,267 --> 00:12:12,500
I no longer have any
feelings for you at all.

179
00:12:12,633 --> 00:12:14,100
Wow.

180
00:12:14,233 --> 00:12:16,233
Straightforward.

181
00:12:16,400 --> 00:12:19,267
I came to the Philippines

182
00:12:19,400 --> 00:12:23,067
to check if I'm still
so crazy in love with you.

183
00:12:23,200 --> 00:12:26,433
But after what I saw today,

184
00:12:26,567 --> 00:12:32,367
I can say I don't feel
anything for you anymore.

185
00:12:32,500 --> 00:12:34,200
So, are we good now?

186
00:12:34,333 --> 00:12:35,800
You got the closure you need.

187
00:12:38,467 --> 00:12:41,033
Darn it.

188
00:12:41,167 --> 00:12:43,200
I'd been a fool
for you for a long time.

189
00:12:48,067 --> 00:12:49,633
At least I'm sure now.

190
00:12:51,333 --> 00:12:55,267
I've forgotten you,
Jade Caparas.

191
00:12:55,400 --> 00:13:00,700
And you can have all the money
you got from me.

192
00:13:00,833 --> 00:13:02,833
I don't need them.

193
00:13:02,967 --> 00:13:05,267
I'm good.

194
00:13:05,400 --> 00:13:06,900
Good for you.

195
00:13:07,033 --> 00:13:09,733
Goodbye, Logan Alvarez.

196
00:13:22,367 --> 00:13:24,167
My gosh, Jade!

197
00:13:25,433 --> 00:13:28,933
You get involved
with all kinds of men.

198
00:13:58,033 --> 00:13:59,533
I hope you're doing okay, Emma.

199
00:14:01,833 --> 00:14:03,567
I hope you're all better now.

200
00:14:06,067 --> 00:14:08,467
Mookie isn't the only one
who misses you.

201
00:14:10,867 --> 00:14:12,367
I miss you, too, Emma.

202
00:14:15,000 --> 00:14:16,433
I miss you so much.

203
00:14:25,000 --> 00:14:26,767
Thank you so much
for recommending Andrea

204
00:14:26,900 --> 00:14:29,533
at Haven Wood, Astrid.

205
00:14:29,700 --> 00:14:31,700
You're welcome, Ma'am Jade.

206
00:14:31,833 --> 00:14:33,467
Come on!

207
00:14:33,600 --> 00:14:35,100
Just call me, Jade.

208
00:14:35,233 --> 00:14:37,900
Okay, Jade.

209
00:14:38,033 --> 00:14:40,833
I'm glad you still entrusted
Artemis Pharmacy to me

210
00:14:40,967 --> 00:14:43,733
even though Olive is gone.

211
00:14:43,867 --> 00:14:45,233
I know, right.

212
00:14:45,367 --> 00:14:48,500
Despite almost betraying Olive
so many times.

213
00:14:50,367 --> 00:14:52,267
Come on, I'm just kidding!

214
00:14:52,400 --> 00:14:54,233
You're so serious.

215
00:14:54,367 --> 00:14:58,067
I know you and Olive
had misunderstandings.

216
00:14:58,200 --> 00:15:01,867
But I also know
how loyal you are to her.

217
00:15:02,033 --> 00:15:04,700
And I hope
you're also loyal to me.

218
00:15:04,833 --> 00:15:06,067
Of course.

219
00:15:06,200 --> 00:15:07,767
You can count on me.

220
00:15:07,900 --> 00:15:09,200
Great.

221
00:15:09,333 --> 00:15:12,800
Go on. Go back to Artemis.
I'll just visit later.

222
00:15:12,933 --> 00:15:16,367
Okay. Thanks again.

223
00:15:16,500 --> 00:15:18,233
- Bye, Astrid.
- Bye.

224
00:15:23,600 --> 00:15:28,600
Lucky you, I don't have any
other friends aside from you.

225
00:15:35,767 --> 00:15:37,600
Hello?

226
00:15:37,733 --> 00:15:39,133
Yes, Andrea?

227
00:15:43,200 --> 00:15:46,167
What?

228
00:15:46,300 --> 00:15:48,167
Emma escaped?

229
00:15:48,300 --> 00:15:50,900
Sorry, Ma'am Jade.

230
00:15:51,033 --> 00:15:54,000
I didn't know
how she got out of the gate.

231
00:15:54,133 --> 00:15:56,833
And a man came.

232
00:15:56,967 --> 00:15:59,333
We couldn't catch her.

233
00:15:59,467 --> 00:16:01,300
Darn you!

234
00:16:01,433 --> 00:16:03,833
I thought I could count on you!

235
00:16:03,967 --> 00:16:06,700
Don't worry, Ma'am.

236
00:16:06,833 --> 00:16:08,733
I injected a lot of drugs
into her.

237
00:16:08,900 --> 00:16:10,533
She's probably so out of it.

238
00:16:10,667 --> 00:16:13,267
She probably
can't think straight.

239
00:16:13,400 --> 00:16:14,500
Maybe she won't manage
to get there.

240
00:16:14,633 --> 00:16:15,800
Believe me.

241
00:16:15,933 --> 00:16:17,533
What she did
can lead to her death.

242
00:16:17,667 --> 00:16:20,533
We're not sure about that!

243
00:16:20,667 --> 00:16:24,600
You'll deal with me
if she gets here.

244
00:16:24,733 --> 00:16:26,700
And Danilo will definitely
find Emma

245
00:16:26,833 --> 00:16:29,600
once he finds out
his wife is missing!

246
00:16:29,733 --> 00:16:31,633
Oh no, Ma'am.

247
00:16:31,767 --> 00:16:36,667
Danilo's here.

248
00:16:36,800 --> 00:16:43,133
Tell him Emma escaped and
has no intention of seeing them.

249
00:16:43,300 --> 00:16:45,167
Sir, how are you?

250
00:16:49,467 --> 00:16:52,633
Based on her recent
symptoms and test results,

251
00:16:53,733 --> 00:16:57,033
it seems that the medications
given to her

252
00:16:57,167 --> 00:16:59,067
aggravated her condition.

253
00:17:00,367 --> 00:17:01,833
So what you're saying, Doc...

254
00:17:03,433 --> 00:17:06,000
they're giving her the wrong
medications in Haven Wood?

255
00:17:06,400 --> 00:17:07,633
It's a possibility.

256
00:17:08,367 --> 00:17:11,400
Or she's given a higher dosage.

257
00:17:13,367 --> 00:17:15,733
Some medications can
trigger side effects

258
00:17:15,900 --> 00:17:19,333
that exacerbate certain
psychiatric symptoms

259
00:17:19,467 --> 00:17:22,333
like paranoia
and hallucinations.

260
00:17:24,200 --> 00:17:27,033
We'll find out

261
00:17:27,167 --> 00:17:31,733
if we go to Haven Wood
to get her medical history.

262
00:17:31,867 --> 00:17:36,733
We can't do that until
we hear what happened to her.

263
00:17:41,667 --> 00:17:43,600
Looks like she was abused there.

264
00:17:47,167 --> 00:17:52,433
I've already adjusted the
patient's medication regimen.

265
00:17:52,600 --> 00:17:54,900
I'll closely monitor her
throughout the process

266
00:17:55,033 --> 00:17:57,467
to ensure her safety
and well-being.

267
00:17:59,567 --> 00:18:03,200
She needs our full support,

268
00:18:03,333 --> 00:18:04,867
especially her family...

269
00:18:05,000 --> 00:18:05,967
if she has any.

270
00:18:12,800 --> 00:18:13,633
What?

271
00:18:14,633 --> 00:18:15,900
Emma escaped?

272
00:18:16,567 --> 00:18:17,567
Yes.

273
00:18:17,700 --> 00:18:21,433
She did that
when she was almost healed.

274
00:18:21,600 --> 00:18:26,167
Actually, she has wanted to be
discharged for several days now.

275
00:18:26,667 --> 00:18:27,867
She wanted to get discharged?

276
00:18:28,000 --> 00:18:29,600
That means she wants
to go home to us.

277
00:18:29,733 --> 00:18:30,800
No.

278
00:18:30,933 --> 00:18:32,900
She doesn't want
to go back to your house.

279
00:18:33,033 --> 00:18:34,133
You know why?

280
00:18:34,933 --> 00:18:36,933
She said you didn't want her.

281
00:18:37,067 --> 00:18:39,267
And you'd bring her back here.

282
00:18:39,400 --> 00:18:42,600
That's why she wanted
to go away.

283
00:18:43,900 --> 00:18:46,133
But you let Emma go.

284
00:18:46,700 --> 00:18:48,933
You let her escape!

285
00:18:49,367 --> 00:18:50,533
That's not true.

286
00:18:50,667 --> 00:18:52,800
What if something bad
happens to my wife?

287
00:18:53,667 --> 00:18:55,833
What if I don't see
my wife again?

288
00:19:23,700 --> 00:19:27,233
You'll go crazy in here.

289
00:19:27,367 --> 00:19:29,233
Don't come near me!
I don't want it anymore!

290
00:19:29,400 --> 00:19:32,900
- You'll die in here.
- No!

291
00:19:33,033 --> 00:19:36,000
- You'll die in here.
- Don't!

292
00:19:36,133 --> 00:19:39,100
- You'll go crazy.
- Don't come near.

293
00:19:39,233 --> 00:19:41,600
Don't come near me!
You'll kill me!

294
00:19:41,733 --> 00:19:43,900
- You'll kill me!
- No, no.

295
00:19:44,033 --> 00:19:45,633
- Demons!
- No.

296
00:19:45,767 --> 00:19:48,167
Don't be scared. We're not evil.

297
00:19:51,100 --> 00:19:52,367
- Hold her.
- Demons!

298
00:19:52,500 --> 00:19:55,233
- Don't come near me!
- We only care for you!

299
00:19:55,367 --> 00:19:58,333
Don't!

300
00:19:58,467 --> 00:20:00,833
- Slowly.
- Wait. Hold on.

301
00:20:00,967 --> 00:20:02,733
Stay still.

302
00:20:02,900 --> 00:20:04,133
Stop!

303
00:20:05,567 --> 00:20:06,867
Stop!

304
00:20:07,000 --> 00:20:09,100
Breathe. Breathe.

305
00:20:09,233 --> 00:20:10,167
Okay?

306
00:20:24,633 --> 00:20:27,333
I told you.

307
00:20:27,467 --> 00:20:30,567
Let's transfer her
to a psychiatric center.

308
00:20:30,700 --> 00:20:33,700
It'll be tough on you.

309
00:20:33,833 --> 00:20:35,667
Look at what she did to you.

310
00:20:43,900 --> 00:20:47,233
Did Mom really say that?

311
00:20:47,367 --> 00:20:49,700
That she's not
coming back anymore?

312
00:20:49,833 --> 00:20:50,767
Yes, dear.

313
00:20:54,067 --> 00:20:56,833
I've talked to the administrator
of Haven Wood.

314
00:20:56,967 --> 00:21:00,400
They'll help us find
your Mommy Emma.

315
00:21:00,533 --> 00:21:04,233
I also spoke to this private
investigator whom I know.

316
00:21:04,367 --> 00:21:08,400
They'll help us locate Emma.

317
00:21:08,567 --> 00:21:10,433
But she doesn't want
to go back anymore.

318
00:21:10,567 --> 00:21:13,000
That's what I'm thinking, too.

319
00:21:13,133 --> 00:21:14,300
Emma's all better now.

320
00:21:14,433 --> 00:21:16,367
She knows what she's doing.

321
00:21:16,500 --> 00:21:20,733
She'll come home
if she wants to be with us.

322
00:21:20,867 --> 00:21:23,800
That means...

323
00:21:23,933 --> 00:21:26,000
Mom doesn't want us anymore.

324
00:21:28,367 --> 00:21:29,233
She doesn't want me anymore.

325
00:21:30,800 --> 00:21:34,800
Baby girl, don't think that way.

326
00:21:34,933 --> 00:21:37,467
We're not sure yet.

327
00:21:37,600 --> 00:21:38,900
Who knows?

328
00:21:39,033 --> 00:21:42,633
Your mom might surprise us.

329
00:21:42,800 --> 00:21:45,533
What if she doesn't?

330
00:21:45,667 --> 00:21:47,867
What if she doesn't come
back anymore?

331
00:21:49,733 --> 00:21:51,767
She didn't even talk to us.

332
00:21:53,600 --> 00:22:00,500
She didn't realize that
everything is for her own good.

333
00:22:02,767 --> 00:22:04,400
I wish she had talked to us.

334
00:22:06,300 --> 00:22:09,867
Maybe we should get
some rest for now.

335
00:22:10,300 --> 00:22:12,733
Let's wait
for Haven Wood's update.

336
00:22:14,200 --> 00:22:15,300
Go on.

337
00:22:15,467 --> 00:22:16,500
Go on, baby girl.

338
00:22:17,800 --> 00:22:18,800
Let's go, dear.

339
00:22:35,400 --> 00:22:36,033
Caloy.

340
00:22:37,033 --> 00:22:41,867
You're lucky I wasn't caught
because of your slip-up.

341
00:22:42,000 --> 00:22:45,867
If you fail again,
you'll deal with me.

342
00:22:46,000 --> 00:22:50,500
Make sure you find Emma
before she comes home.

343
00:22:50,967 --> 00:22:52,567
Do you understand?

344
00:23:02,300 --> 00:23:03,867
Emma got hurt. Didn't she?

345
00:23:08,133 --> 00:23:10,433
I don't want
to get separated from her.

346
00:23:10,567 --> 00:23:14,333
I want us to be together
once she gets better.

347
00:23:14,467 --> 00:23:17,067
But she didn't realize that.

348
00:23:19,867 --> 00:23:24,167
Danilo, you've had
more than enough.

349
00:23:24,333 --> 00:23:26,967
Drink slowly.

350
00:23:27,100 --> 00:23:34,167
Maybe Emma has a reason
why she went away.

351
00:23:34,300 --> 00:23:36,900
No matter how I think about it,

352
00:23:38,533 --> 00:23:42,433
I can't understand
why she left us.

353
00:23:44,733 --> 00:23:46,400
You know what?

354
00:23:46,533 --> 00:23:50,500
I can see in Mookie's eyes
how hurt she is.

355
00:23:50,633 --> 00:23:52,967
Because she won't see
her mom again.

356
00:24:01,167 --> 00:24:07,267
I also don't understand
why Emma did that

357
00:24:09,967 --> 00:24:14,667
after we did
what was best for her.

358
00:24:17,600 --> 00:24:19,767
You know what, Danilo?

359
00:24:19,900 --> 00:24:21,233
To be honest...

360
00:24:22,933 --> 00:24:26,600
I feel ashamed
of what my sister did.

361
00:24:28,600 --> 00:24:32,733
And I apologize
for everything she's done.

362
00:24:36,967 --> 00:24:38,067
Danilo...

363
00:24:39,233 --> 00:24:40,233
don't worry.

364
00:24:42,400 --> 00:24:44,933
I'm ready to fill in
Emma's shortcomings

365
00:24:45,067 --> 00:24:46,433
with you and Mookie.

366
00:24:48,900 --> 00:24:51,567
Even if it means

367
00:24:51,700 --> 00:24:53,833
that I have to be
Mookie's mother.

368
00:24:57,400 --> 00:25:00,633
I'll help you, Danilo.

369
00:25:00,767 --> 00:25:03,900
I'll help you and Mookie
forget about her.

370
00:25:06,400 --> 00:25:08,267
But you know what, Jade?

371
00:25:10,133 --> 00:25:12,900
I fell shy towards you because
I think that's too much.

372
00:25:13,033 --> 00:25:15,700
It's not your obligation
to do it for us.

373
00:25:19,833 --> 00:25:22,733
But Danilo...

374
00:25:22,867 --> 00:25:24,667
I love what I do.

375
00:25:31,200 --> 00:25:33,200
I've been alone for so long.

376
00:25:35,700 --> 00:25:37,233
I'm always alone.

377
00:25:39,467 --> 00:25:41,900
I have no family by my side.

378
00:25:44,700 --> 00:25:46,900
You.

379
00:25:47,033 --> 00:25:48,667
You and Mookie...

380
00:25:51,733 --> 00:25:53,833
you'll be my family.

381
00:26:04,800 --> 00:26:08,233
I've got information
about the woman you're helping.

382
00:26:08,400 --> 00:26:10,767
Her name is Emma Joseco.

383
00:26:10,900 --> 00:26:13,333
I want to get to know
that woman better.

384
00:26:13,467 --> 00:26:15,167
Don't bring me back
to Haven Wood.

385
00:26:15,300 --> 00:26:17,567
They're making me crazy.
I won't get better.

386
00:26:17,700 --> 00:26:18,800
On one condition...

387
00:26:18,933 --> 00:26:23,533
I can't promise that I'll
be as good as your mom.

388
00:26:23,667 --> 00:26:26,267
But I will try my very best

389
00:26:26,400 --> 00:26:29,167
to take good care of you
and your dad.

390
00:26:29,300 --> 00:26:33,367
So, baby girl, I hope you
also treat me as your mom.

391
00:26:33,500 --> 00:26:36,967
Is that okay?

392
00:26:37,100 --> 00:26:38,500
Mookie!

393
00:26:38,633 --> 00:26:41,200
I feel like
they don't want me anymore.

394
00:26:41,333 --> 00:26:43,700
Because they never came
back to see me in Haven Wood.

395
00:26:43,867 --> 00:26:46,733
But I have a bad feeling
about Jade.

396
00:26:46,867 --> 00:26:49,400
- Jade?
- Jade Caparas.
